---
import Button from '@/components/Button.astro';
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Popular">
  <article>
    <h1 class="h1" transition:name="hero">
      The bright future of Web 3.0: promise fulfilled?
    </h1>
    <p class="p">
      Web 3.0 is shaping up to be the next big revolution in the internet,
      promising an era of decentralization and empowerment for users. Unlike
      previous versions of the web, dominated by tech giants that control our
      data and content, Web 3.0 seeks to democratize the internet. The central
      idea is to create an internet where platforms are not owned by a single
      entity, but by the users who build and use them. Technologies such as
      blockchain, smart contracts, and non-fungible tokens (NFTs) are the
      pillars that support this vision.
    </p>
    <p class="p">
      This new web is not just about owning digital assets, but about having a
      real voice and participation in platform governance. Users will be able to
      vote on changes, receive rewards for their contributions, and ultimately
      own a part of the network. This could transform entire industries, from
      decentralized finance (DeFi) to content creation and gaming. However,
      legitimate questions remain: Is Web 3.0 accessible to everyone? Don't its
      complex technologies make it difficult for most people to understand? And,
      more importantly, is it really delivering on its promise to give power
      back to the people, or is it just creating new types of intermediaries?
      The future of Web 3.0 is undoubtedly bright, but its path to mass adoption
      and the fulfillment of its ideals remains to be seen.
    </p>
  </article>
  <Button />
</Layout>
